{{Infobox person | name = Max Rössler | birth_date = 1940 | education = [[ETH Zurich]] | occupation = Swiss Investor }}
'''Max Rössler''' (born 1940) is a [[Switzerland|Swiss]] [[investor]] and [[Patronage|patron]].
== Life == Rössler attended the Kantonsschule at Burggraben in St. Gallen, where he finished his [[Matura|matriculation]]. He then studied mathematics at [[ETH Zurich]], where he co-authored a dissertation on railway computations in the field of [[Celestial mechanics|space mechanics]] in 1966 with [[Eduard Stiefel]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.research-collection.ethz.ch/handle/20.500.11850/133750 |title=Analytische Störungstheorie im Dreikörperproblem mit Hilfe von regularisierenden Variablen |author=Max Rössler |date=1966 |publisher=ETH Zürich |access-date=26 October 2017}}</ref> He then spent time at [[Harvard University]] in [[Cambridge, Massachusetts]], for a [[NASA]] research project to calculate space travel. Subsequently, he was a lecturer for applied mathematics and [[operations research]] at ETH [[Zürich|Zurich]].<ref name="A">{{cite web |url=https://www.ethz.ch/content/dam/ethz/main/news/eth-tag/dokumente/2013/131116_Laudatio_Ehrenraete_Braginsky_Haefner_Roessler.pdf |title=Laudatio für die Ehrenräte René Braginsky, Martin Haefner und Dr. Max Rössler |date=16 November 2013 |publisher=ETH Zürich |access-date=26 October 2017}}</ref>
In 1978 Rössler changed to finances. He was responsible for the analysis department of fixed interest investments and the management of investment funds of CHF 12 billion at the [[Credit Suisse|Schweizerische Kreditanstalt]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://rsb-securities.ch/ |title=Personen Max Rössler |publisher=RSB Securities |access-date=26 October 2017}}</ref> Later he was responsible for financial investments of the [[Suva (insurer)|Swiss Accident Insurance Institution]] (SUVA). He successfully used his knowledge in the financial sector for his own investments, to which a considerable amount of his assets includes investments in several Swiss companies. He is the main shareholder of the Parmino Holding AG which includes the construction company [[Implenia]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nzz.ch/der_implenia-goenner-1.4055650 |title=Der Implenia-Gönner |date=24 November 2009 |publisher=Neue Zürcher Zeitung |access-date=26 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.implenia.com/de-ch/investoren/die-aktie.html |title=Kotiert an der SIX Swiss Exchange |date=6 March 2006 |publisher=Implenia |access-date=26 October 2017}}</ref> Through his influence on the occupation of the Implenia management team, Rössler became well known to the public.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tagesanzeiger.ch/wirtschaft/unternehmen-und-konjunktur/Weitere-Ruecktritte-bei-Implenia/story/12757256 |title=Weitere Rücktritte bei Implenia |author=Benita Vogel |date=18 February 2016 |publisher=Tages Anzeiger |access-date=26 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.handelszeitung.ch/unternehmen/machtkampf-bei-implenia-sorgt-fuer-kritik-994450 |title=Machtkampf bei Implenia sorgt für Kritik |author=Bernhard Fischer, Marcel Speiser |date=17 February 2016 |publisher=Handelszeitung |access-date=26 October 2017}}</ref>
In addition, Rössler holds a major stake in the machine tool business Starrag Group and is a board member of other companies such as RSB Securities AG, Global Care and SunVesta Holding.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sunvesta.com/index.php?id=39 |title=Dr. Max Rössler |publisher=SunVesta Holding |access-date=26 October 2017}}</ref> He is also an advisor to Swiss private banks. Rössler is a member of the Board of Trustees at the Rütli Foundation, which is affiliated to the private bank [[Reichmuth & Co]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ruetli-stiftung.ch/kontakt.html |title=Stiftungsräte |publisher=Rütli-Stiftung |access-date=26 October 2017}}</ref>
== Max-Rössler-Prize == His private wealth enabled him to [[Donation|donate]] largely. In 2009, Rössler funded the annual Max-Rössler-Prize for the support of outstanding young professors at the ETH Zurich. The prize money amounted to CHF 200,000.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ethz.ch/de/forschung/wissenschaftspreise-und-veranstaltungen/roessler-preis.html |title=Rössler Preis |publisher=ETH Zürich |access-date=26 October 2017}}</ref> Another major donation, together with the [[Walter Haefner]] Foundation, enabled the founding of the new Institute for Theoretical Studies at ETH Zurich 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.blick.ch/news/schweiz/hochschule-eth-zuerich-gruendet-institut-fuer-theoretische-studien-id2304357.html |title=ETH Zürich gründet Institut für Theoretische Studien |date=15 May 2013 |publisher=Blick |access-date=26 October 2017}}</ref>
